2Q revenue fell \(1\%\) y- y to Rmb56bn, \(4\%\) above MSe. By segment, \(1\%\) growth in 1H25 was supported by engines rising \(3\%\) , partly offset by a \(2\%\) decline at KION. Within the engine segment, large- bore engines were the key growth driver with 5k units of sales in 1H, up \(41\%\) y- y, including \(\sim 600\) units from data centers, up \(491\%\) Meanwhile, Weichai's HDT engines declined \(22\%\) y- y to 125k units in 1H, implying a market share loss; diesel and LNG HDT industry sales fell \(3\%\) in aggregate during the same period.

2Q GPM continued to improve to \(22.1\%\) , up 0.3ppt y- y, supported mainly by the engine segment; parentco GPM rose 3.3ppts to \(31.9\%\) in 1H. This was offset by a higher opex ratio (+0.8ppt) with less operating leverage.

2Q net profit declined \(11\%\) y- y to Rmb2.9bn, \(3\%\) below MSe, partly dragged by an \(83\%\) increase in impairment loss to Rmb535mn. Weichai declared an interim dividend with the payout ratio at \(55\%\) , same as in 1H24. The KION one- off impact to Weichai's NP in 2Q was limited to Rmb14mn.
Source: Company data, Morgan Stanley Research

We apply an A- H premium of \(12\%\) (its 5- year historical average), resulting in our A- share price target of Rmb17.7. We also apply a HKD/Rmb exchange rate of 0.9.
- Stronger-than-expected earnings contribution from KION- Better-than-expected volume growth in engine and HDT sales- Expanding A-H premium
- Slower-than-expected FAI growth- Market share loss in engine/HDT market- A-H premium compression

Base case, 12x 2025e P/E. This is largely in line with its 8- year historical average 1- year forward P/E of 11x, which we view as appropriate because: 1) the HDT industry should be in a mild upcycle in 2025- 26, supporting earnings growth for WeiChai; and 2) solid demand for the large- bore engine business should benefit from domestic AI capex acceleration, which is still at an early stage. This should also improve sentiment and stimulate re- rating.
